changelog.comment: New Entry. Reviewer 1 changed databaseID references to fit strain described in publication, added 4-phosphopantetheine cofactor, added alternative reaction using leucine instead of phenylalanine.

reactions.description: amide bond formation between arginine, encoded by the A domain of the NRPS-like gene, and phenylalanine provided by their cognate aminoacyl-tRNAs as substrate.
amide bond formation between arginine, encoded by the A domain of the NRPS-like gene, and leucine provided by their cognate aminoacyl-tRNAs as substrate.
